cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep recurrent neural network model to predict the probability of an action being the last in a session. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with modelling student behavior in an online educational system, which can be seen as a form of computational science. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses log data from a system where students can learn mathematics through various kinds of learning materials, as well as multiple types of exercises, which involves natural language processing. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with predicting the end of a session in an educational system, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper aims to optimize the way content is presented and consumed in an educational system, which involves human-computer interaction.
